So then, again,
one, don't round--

00:21:55.763 --> 00:21:57.430
because we've had
times when folks said,

00:21:57.430 --> 00:21:59.380
ah, this is about 931.

00:21:59.380 --> 00:22:01.922
And when you're
off by half an MeV,

00:22:01.922 --> 00:22:03.880
you could be at a totally
different decay level

00:22:03.880 --> 00:22:05.838
or get a positive Q when
it should be negative,

00:22:05.838 --> 00:22:07.050
or vice versa.

00:22:07.050 --> 00:22:09.220
And let's take a quick
look here to say,

00:22:09.220 --> 00:22:15.292
if this atomic mass
is 31.9720707 AMU--

00:22:15.292 --> 00:22:16.750
this is why I
