And A is 32.

00:42:40.740 --> 00:42:42.222
Thank you.

00:42:42.222 --> 00:42:42.930
Yeah, good point.

00:42:42.930 --> 00:42:43.847
Let me try this again.

00:43:12.865 --> 00:43:16.500
Ah, I know what I'm doing wrong.

00:43:16.500 --> 00:43:20.340
This part right here, we
want to convert to AMU.

00:43:20.340 --> 00:43:23.400
So we can take our minus--

00:43:23.400 --> 00:43:32.670
thank you-- 26.015 MeV
per c squared and divide

00:43:32.670 --> 00:43:38.544
by our conversion
factor, 931.49--

00:43:38.544 --> 00:43:42.350
let's see-- MeV per
c squared per AMU.

00:43:45.070 --> 00:43:46.590
What does that give us?

00:43:46.590 --> 00:43:51.850
26.015 over that.

00:43:51.850 --> 00:44:00.630
0.027928 AMU negative.

00:44:00.630 --> 00:44:02.460
Let's put that in
and see how we do.

00:44:13.370 --> 00:44:24.330
So plus 0.027928 minus 32.

00:44:24.330 --> 00:44:28.440
And then we get 271.--

00:44:28.440 --> 00:44:32.530
I'll just say 764 MeV.

00:44:32.530 --> 00:44:34.630
I think six digits is enough.

00:44:34.630 --> 00:44:38.770
The actual binding
energy, 271.780 MeV,

00:44:38.770 --> 00:44:41.650
so we're off by 16
electron volts--

00:44:41.650 --> 00:44:43.060
close enough.

00:44:43.060 --> 00:44:45.710
Also note that I used a
five-digit accurate conversion

00:44:45.710 --> 00:44:46.210
factor.

00:44:46.210 --> 00:44:47.460
That might be part
